{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nKeep the single-instance bot alive under hangs, controllable in an incident, and — critically — **crash-safe**: a restart must never double-submit or strand a stack. This is the reliability-fallback backbone. Split out of S5 (`perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon`).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/autolander/loop.py` — EDIT: heartbeat write, emergency-stop sentinel check, SIGTERM drain + recovery-record write, restart-recovery reconciliation.\n- `infra/compose/Dockerfile.autolander` — EDIT: the `HEALTHCHECK`.\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml` — EDIT: set `stop_grace_period: 120s` on the autolander service (so the SIGTERM drain can write `recovery.json`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] **Heartbeat (AC5):** the bot writes a timestamp file in the state volume once per its 15 s poll (S2 cadence); its age is served as `heartbeat_age_s` by S5c's status endpoint. Contract: freshness ≤ 15 s; `land`'s `lander_down` treats age **> 90 s** (6× poll) as down.\n- [ ] **Liveness/restart (AC4):** a `HEALTHCHECK` marks the container `unhealthy` on a **hang** by stat-ing the **local heartbeat file** (unhealthy if older than the staleness threshold) — it MUST NOT probe Gerrit (a Gerrit outage would flap restarts). The `willfarrell/autoheal` sidecar (S5a) restarts the `autoheal=true`-labeled container on `unhealthy`.\n- [ ] **Emergency-stop (prior art: Zuul `pause`):** an emergency-stop **sentinel file** in the state volume (presence = stop; operator creates to pause, removes to resume) transitions the bot to `paused` (the S2 `phase` value) — STOPS consuming new `Autosubmit` changes. Lives on the state volume so a redeploy does not silently un-pause.\n- [ ] **Drain-on-shutdown + crash-safe recovery (RELIABILITY FALLBACK):** on SIGTERM the bot finishes the in-flight `wipChain`, writes its outcome to S3's marker, then exits (prior art: Zuul `graceful`); the drain does NOT wait out a full CI cycle — on SIGTERM it either finishes an already-near-complete submit or **immediately writes a concrete recovery record** (`recovery.json` in the state volume: the `wipChain` snapshot — `change_id`, `chain_member_ids`, `tested_shas`, `phase`, `re_drive_count`, and the handback `acknowledged` flag) and exits. The drain is **time-bounded to 120 s**, and the compose service sets **`stop_grace_period: 120s`** so Docker does not SIGKILL the bot before it can write `recovery.json` (Docker's default `stop_grace_period` is only 10 s — far too short; without this the recovery record would be lost). **On restart** the bot reads `recovery.json` + reconciles against LIVE Gerrit and S3's markers BEFORE selecting new work, with a decision rule for **every** kill-point phase:\n  - `phase=rebasing` — a rebase may or may not have minted a new patchset; discard the in-memory `wipChain` and **re-select from scratch** (the `Autosubmit` label is still set and Gerrit holds the current patchset, so re-selection resumes correctly and idempotently). No submit happened, so nothing to undo.\n  - `phase=awaiting_verified` — the rebase completed (a new patchset exists) and the bot was waiting for CI; discard the in-memory state and **re-select** — the change is still `Autosubmit`+needs-fresh-`Verified`, so the loop re-enters `awaiting_verified` for the same patchset. Idempotent; no submit happened.\n  - `phase=submitting` (mid-submit) — check LIVE Gerrit: all members `MERGED` → write the `merged` outcome/ack; not merged → **re-drive** (re-verify FFO-landability, re-await, re-submit). Never blindly re-issue submit.\n  - mid-handback — complete the idempotent `Autosubmit`-removal across the stack, keyed by S3's `acknowledged=false`, then set `acknowledged=true`.\n  No double-submit; no stranded stack.\n- [ ] **Crash-recovery/idempotency test (the reliability guarantee):** an automated test kills the bot at each phase (`rebasing`, `awaiting_verified`, `submitting`, mid-handback) and asserts the restarted instance neither double-submits nor strands a stack, and converges the S3 marker to `acknowledged=true`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783838784472117001,"uuid":"1c8ea626-9822-4b52-9898-f8625a95f0eb"}